A photorealistic aerial view of a busy urban intersection in Singapore at golden hour, showing a lone cyclist in bright cycling gear navigating through multiple lanes of traffic. The scene captures the tension between vulnerability and determination—the small figure on two wheels surrounded by cars and buses, their long shadow stretching across the warm asphalt. Tropical trees line the streets, and distinctive Singapore HDB apartment blocks rise in the background against an orange-pink sky. Motion blur on the surrounding vehicles emphasizes movement while the cyclist remains sharp and focused, positioned strategically in the center of a turning lane rather than hugging the edge.
